1) Install Python with Pip via Homebrew by following instructions here: http://docs.python-guide.org/en/latest/starting/install/osx/
2) Install Java here: http://www.oracle.com/technetwork/java/javase/downloads/jdk8-downloads-2133151.html
3) Install Sass: sudo gem install sass -v 3.3.4
4) Get added to Ocado Technology Git Hub repositories
5) Clone repositories: codeforlife-deploy; codeforlife-portal and ocargo
6) Within codeforlife-delpoy/submodules create symbolic links to codeforlife-portal and ocargo names 'portal' and 'ocargo' respectively. Do this by running the folloing in the command line: $ln -s ../../codeforlife-portal portal then $ln -s ../../ocargo ocargo
7) Within codeforlife-deploy run ./build.sh
8) Within codeforlife-deploy run ./manage.py migrate
9) Run: ./manage.py collectstatic
10) Within codeforlife-deploy run ./manage.py runserver






